{
  "text": "Earlier optimal gestational age at delivery in monochorionic twins, compared to dichorionic twins, is not well understood. The higher risk of adverse neonatal outcome in monochorionic twins is considered to be the possible predisposing factor, requiring early delivery [CITATION_1] . In monochorionic twins, a single placenta is shared by each twin, which may result in imbalanced vascular anastomosis followed by an ischemic injury and hypovolemia [CITATION_2] . Because the degree of vascular anastomosis vary greatly, the imbalance of blood flow level also has variation, which can cause minor complications that are diffi-",
